params._timeout: Timeout in AEST as UNIX timestamp

deliveryStatus(bool).details: Oracle submit asset delivery status. If asset is delivered locked payment is released to the beneficiary and the  contract is destroyed. Otherwise, do nothing

redeem().details: Request to redeem as beneficiary. Once the request is made oracle is informed to report status via CheckDelivery event

release().details: Request to release funds as funder. Once the notification  is made oracle is informed via CheckTime event

timeoutStatus(bool).details: Oracle submit timeout status. If timeout reached locked payment is released to the funder and the  contract is destroyed. Otherwise, do nothing

devdoc.title: Escrow contract This contract locks ETH until the delivery of asset is confirmed or timeout is reached. To check the delivery and wall clock time, we rely on an off-chain oracle.
